			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="http://theppl.us/dnc2012/files/2012/09/7931764168_b1e43f3fea_b-485x323.jpeg" alt="" width="485" height="323" /><iframe width="480" height="296" src="http://www.ustream.tv/embed/recorded/25167977?wmode=direct" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border: 0px none transparent;">    </iframe><br /><a href="http://www.ustream.tv/" style="padding: 2px 0px 4px; width: 400px; background: #ffffff; display: block; color: #000000; font-weight: normal; font-size: 10px; text-decoration: underline; text-align: center;" target="_blank">Video streaming by Ustream</a><p>With voter suppression alone considered just &#8220;the tip of the iceberg,&#8221; this panel discussed the heavy hitting issues of voter rights and equality.  From voter identification to redistricting, the our speakers drew attention to issues that affect every American.</p>
<p>The panel consisted of Rev. William Barber, Robert Dawkins, Atty. Ann S. Jacobs, and Michael Morrill.  The group brought experience from grassroots organizing, community involvement, and the NAACP to our stage in a conversation based essentially on voter equality.</p>
<p>To hear the awesome conversation, check out the video above.</p>
